### 1. Install pip & jupyter 

```
#apt install python3-pip
#pip install jupyter --upgrade --proxy http://w.x.y.z
#pip install ipython==6.5  --proxy http://w.x.y.z
```
### 2. Setup the UFW to allow access to jupyter
```
#ufw allow from 10.150.62.0/24 proto tcp to any port 8080 comment 'Allow from IT/IS Subnet to Jupyter'
```

### 3. Create a file `jupyter.service` 
```
# mkdir /usr/lib/systemd/system/
# vim  /usr/lib/systemd/system/jupyter.service
```
as below 

```
[Unit]
Description=Jupyter Notebook

[Service]
Type=simple
PIDFile=/run/jupyter.pid
#Jupyter Notebook location
ExecStart=/usr/local/bin/jupyter-notebook --config=/home/ben/.jupyter/jupyter_notebook_config.py
User=ben
Group=ben
WorkingDirectory=/home/ben/
Restart=always
RestartSec=10
#KillMode=mixed

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```
### 4. Enable the service
```
#systemctl enable jupyter.service
#systemctl daemon-reload
#systemctl restart jupyter.service
#systemctl status jupyter.service
```
